# Project Rules - Données Lumières

> Stack: Next.js 16 + dbt + BigQuery
> Docs détaillés: `docs/architecture-modelling.md`, `docs/architecture-frontend.md`

## Project Structure
pipeline/          # dbt models + scripts d'export
website/           # Next.js app
docs/              # Architecture docs

## Critical Business Logic (MUST READ)

### Anti-Double Counting
- Use ONLY `Type d'opération = 'Réel'` (exclude 'Pour Ordre')
- Never sum `Montant AP` (use `Mandaté après régul.`)
- Subventions are a SUBSET of budget, not an addition

### Data Sources
- Truth source: `core_budget` (from `stg_budget_principal`)
- Subventions enrichies: `core_subventions`
- See `docs/architecture-modelling.md` for full data lineage

## Conventions

### dbt/SQL
- French column names in models
- Naming: `stg_*`, `int_*`, `core_*`, `mart_*`
- OBT (One Big Table) per entity design for core layer

### Frontend
- Static JSON in `website/public/data/` (no live BigQuery calls)
- French UI text, French number formatting
- Dark theme (slate-800/900)

### Shared Tab Components (website/src/components/shared/)
Les pages Subventions, Investissements et Logements partagent une architecture 3 onglets (Annuel/Tendances/Explorer) via des composants partagés. Chaque page fournit un **thin wrapper** avec sa config (breakdowns, couleurs, colonnes, filtres).

| Composant partagé | Rôle | Pages |
|---|---|---|
| `AnnuelTab.tsx` | Treemap ECharts + breakdown selector + KPI cards + table preview | Subventions, Investissements |
| `TendancesTab.tsx` | Stacked bar chart + variation ranking + KPIs + year range | Subventions, Investissements, Logements |
| `ExplorerTab.tsx` | Layout responsive (sidebar filtres / collapsible mobile) + toggle Liste/Carte/Arrondissements | Subventions, Investissements, Logements |

**Pattern** : `shared/XxxTab.tsx` (générique, configurable via props) → `{domain}/XxxTab.tsx` (thin wrapper avec config domaine) → `app/{domain}/page.tsx` (page Next.js).

**Thèmes** : `purple` (Subventions), `amber` (Investissements), `emerald` (Logements).

**Règle** : toute modification UX commune doit être faite dans le composant partagé, pas dupliquée dans chaque wrapper.

## Responsive Design Strategy

- **Approche mixte** : Responsive CSS par défaut, layouts séparés si nécessaire
- **Breakpoints** : mobile (<768px), tablet (768-1024px), desktop (>1024px)
- **Interactions** : hover (desktop) → tap (mobile), tooltips → drawers/modals
- **Animations** : 300ms max, respecter `prefers-reduced-motion`

### Par composant :
| Type | Mobile | Desktop |
|------|--------|---------|
| Donut/Pie | Tap drill-down, légende bas | Hover, légende latérale |
| Line/Bar charts | Responsive, scroll horizontal si besoin | Complet |
| Sankey | Treemap ou liste interactive | Sankey complet |
| Map | Touch gestures, popup simplifié | Hover, panel latéral |

## Commands
- dbt: `cd pipeline && dbt run`
- Export: `python pipeline/scripts/export/export_all.py`
- Website: `cd website && npm run dev`## 12. Git Safety

- **⚠️ NEVER push to origin main** without explicit user request
- Always push to current feature branch (e.g., git push origin theo2)
- If user says 'push to main', ask for confirmation first
